<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Government propositions and reports </h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p>Government propositions and reports are documents presented to the Storting (Parliament). The documents are made by the ministries, and have the form of recommendations about what the Storting should decide.</p>
<p>Report to the Storting (St.meld.) are used when the Government wants to present issues for the Storting without proposing a decision. Reports to the Storting are often written in the form of a report of work done in a specific area, or a discussion of future politics. The reports, and the processing in the Storting, often form the basis of a proposition.</p>
<p>Propositions to the Storting (St.prp.) are used when the Government asks the Storting to make a decision that is not related to a law. This could be propositions related to the state budget or other propositions for decisions. <br /></p>
  </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
